# UI Debug Workflow

When the user reports a UI issue or requests a frontend change:

## Step 1: Check existing screenshots

Look for cached Playwright screenshots at `~/Desktop/bitlink-screenshots/`.
Read the relevant screenshot to understand the current state before making changes.

## Step 2: If screenshot is missing or stale, capture fresh ones

Run a Playwright script against `http://localhost:3003` to capture the target view:

```typescript
// Use: viewport 393x852, deviceScaleFactor 2.75, isMobile: true
// Save to: ~/Desktop/bitlink-screenshots/<view-name>.png
```

Key views and how to reach them:

- `01-login-page.png` — initial page
- `02-feed.png` — after login, Feed tab
- `03-following.png` — Following tab
- `04-chat-list.png` — Chat tab
- `05-profile.png` — Me tab
- `07-post-detail.png` — click a post
- `10-trust-detail.png` — Profile > Trust Score

## Step 3: Read the screenshot, identify the issue

Use the Read tool on the PNG file to visually inspect and confirm the problem.

## Step 4: Fix the code

Make the necessary changes in source files.

## Step 5: Re-screenshot to verify

Capture a fresh screenshot of the same view, **save it to `~/Desktop/bitlink-screenshots/`**, and read it to confirm the fix works.
Repeat steps 4-5 until the UI matches expectations.

## Screenshot Persistence Rules

- **Every** screenshot (initial check or verification) MUST be saved to `~/Desktop/bitlink-screenshots/`.
- Use descriptive filenames: `feed.png`, `post-detail.png`, `header-v2.png`, `inline-comment.png`, etc.
- Verification screenshots should overwrite or update the relevant view file so the latest state is always cached.
- At the start of any new UI task, **always read the most recent saved screenshot first** to understand the current state before making changes. This avoids unnecessary re-captures.

## Screenshot Naming Convention

Core views use numbered prefixes so they sort naturally:

| View | Filename |
|------|----------|
| Login page | `01-login-page.png` |
| Feed (main home) | `02-feed.png` |
| Following tab | `03-following.png` |
| Chat list | `04-chat-list.png` |
| Profile (Me tab) | `05-profile.png` |
| Trust score page | `06-trust-score.png` |
| Transactions | `07-transactions.png` |
| Settings | `08-settings.png` |
| New post editor | `09-new-post-editor.png` |
| Post detail | `10-post-detail.png` |
| Followers list | `11-followers-list.png` |

Feature-specific screenshots use plain descriptive names:
- `inline-comment.png` — comment input popup on feed
- `search-results.png` — search view with results
- Name must be **immediately understandable** — anyone reading the filename should know exactly what view/feature it shows.

**Cleanup rule**: After iterating on a design (e.g. `header-v1.png`, `header-v2.png`), delete intermediate files and only keep the final result saved under the canonical name (e.g. update `02-feed.png`). Never leave stale iteration files behind.

## Important

- Screenshots dir: `/Users/the053/Desktop/bitlink-screenshots/`
- Dev server: `http://localhost:3003`
- Playwright config: `ui/playwright.config.ts`
- Test file: `ui/tests/screenshot-capture.spec.ts`
- Always verify fixes visually — never assume a code change looks correct without a screenshot.
